qas.question: Which courts decisions are binding across the entire United States?
Which court is the only one able to determine constitutionality?
Which power are inferior courts unable to exercise?
Which courts' decisions, other than Supreme Court, are binding across the country?
Which is the only court unable to determine constitutionality?

context: A common misperception is that <a0_0>the <b1_0><b4_0>Supreme Court<b4_0/><b1_0/><a0_0/> is the only court that may <b2_0>determine constitutionality<b2_0/>; the power is exercised even by the <b3_0>inferior courts<b3_0/>. But only Supreme Court decisions are binding across the nation. Decisions of a Court of Appeals, for instance, are binding only in the circuit over which the court has jurisdiction.
